  "body": "In the description of the CALL and CREATE instructions on page 37, formulas for \\mu'_g are given. However, they seem wrong to me. To my understanding, these definitions would mean that calling an externally-owned account or creating a contract with empty initialization code would essentially be free operations, as no code would need to be executed and hence the formulas would then be equivalent to \\mu'_g = \\mu_g. Clearly, they modify the global state, which should be priced accordingly. So either there is something wrong with these definitions or maybe I am missing something?",
